http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/GRP-reaches-rail-passengers-through-twitter/article13992010.ece

The Government Railway Police (GRP) in Tamil Nadu to reach a bigger audience has tapped the social media. The GRP has launched Railway Police CNI (@grpchennai) on twitter recently.A senior official of GRP said the department felt there was a need to interact with rail passengers on a wider platform and so twitter has been choson. Highlighting the department has been getting positive feedback for its presence on the social media, he said by using twitter information about the various activities of the GRP could be reached real time. Also the social media platform could be used for sharing railway awareness issues and contact details to reach the public.The official pointed out a small team is engaged in feeding live tweets to the public.